content:
To prevent outages for customers who haven’t yet upgraded to the latest version of your mobile app, clone your Messaging for In-App deployment before releasing a new feature. Roll out the new feature on the cloned version of the deployment while allowing customers who haven’t yet upgraded to keep using the older version.

Available in: Lightning Experience
This article applies to:	Messaging for In-App channels

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up this feature:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata Through Metadata API Functions

From Setup, enter Embedded Service Deployments.
Select Embedded Service Deployments from the dropdown menu.
Select Clone from the dropdown menu to the right of your deployment.
Give your cloned deployment a name and confirm that the correct Messaging Channel is referenced.
Save your changes.
Publish your new, cloned deployment.
title: Cloning Messaging for In-App Deployment in Service Cloud
